  "text": "voltammetric and polarization measurements, Spataru et al. confirmed that the functional group, SO 3 H, of cysteic acid (7) can be strongly adsorbed at GC electrode [CITATION_1] . This mechanism is achieved using the L-cysteine solutions prepared with PBS, showing a fast decrease in the peaks response due to a high absorption rate. This outcome is in agreement with the data reported by us, where we observed this behaviour during the electrochemical preparation of modified electrode to PBS solution than HCl solution (see Figure 1) .",
